<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Await on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/await/</link><description>Recent content in Await on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/await/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] Python SyntaxError — 'async' Outside Function</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/python/async-await/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/python/async-await/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="syntaxerror--async-outside-function"&gt;SyntaxError — &amp;lsquo;async&amp;rsquo; Outside Function&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;code&gt;SyntaxError&lt;/code&gt; with the message &amp;ldquo;&amp;lsquo;async&amp;rsquo; outside function&amp;rdquo; is raised when you use the &lt;code&gt;async&lt;/code&gt; keyword outside of a function body. &lt;code&gt;async&lt;/code&gt; can only be used to define asynchronous functions or asynchronous context managers/for loops inside functions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;async&lt;/code&gt; keyword is used to define asynchronous functions (coroutines) in Python 3.5+. When used outside a function, it causes a &lt;code&gt;SyntaxError&lt;/code&gt;. The &lt;code&gt;async def&lt;/code&gt; syntax creates a coroutine that can be awaited using &lt;code&gt;await&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Python SyntaxError — 'await' Outside Async Function</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/python/await-outside-async/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/python/await-outside-async/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="syntaxerror--await-outside-async-function"&gt;SyntaxError — &amp;lsquo;await&amp;rsquo; Outside Async Function&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;code&gt;SyntaxError&lt;/code&gt; with the message &amp;ldquo;&amp;lsquo;await&amp;rsquo; outside async function&amp;rdquo; is raised when you use the &lt;code&gt;await&lt;/code&gt; keyword outside of an &lt;code&gt;async def&lt;/code&gt; function. &lt;code&gt;await&lt;/code&gt; can only be used inside asynchronous functions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;await&lt;/code&gt; keyword is used to pause execution of an async function until the awaited coroutine completes. It can only be used inside &lt;code&gt;async def&lt;/code&gt; functions. Using &lt;code&gt;await&lt;/code&gt; in a regular function or at the module level causes a &lt;code&gt;SyntaxError&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Rust Async/Await Error — Async Function Not Found</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/rust/async-await-2/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/rust/async-await-2/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="asyncawait-error--async-function-not-found"&gt;Async/Await Error — Async Function Not Found&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Errors related to async/await in Rust include &amp;ldquo;async function not found&amp;rdquo;, &amp;ldquo;future is not Send&amp;rdquo;, or &amp;ldquo;missing async runtime&amp;rdquo;. These occur when async code is misused or the ecosystem is misconfigured.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Rust&amp;rsquo;s async/await is zero-cost and requires a runtime (like tokio) to execute. The compiler generates state machines for async functions but doesn&amp;rsquo;t include a runtime. Common issues:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Missing runtime&lt;/strong&gt; — async code has no executor.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Not Send/Sync&lt;/strong&gt; — future can&amp;rsquo;t be sent across threads.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Missing .await&lt;/strong&gt; — forgetting to await a future.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Blocking in async&lt;/strong&gt; — sync operations blocking the runtime.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-rust" data-lang="rust"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 1: Forgetting .await
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;async&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;fn&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;get_data&lt;/span&gt;() -&amp;gt; String { &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;data&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;.to_string() }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;#[tokio::main]&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;async&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;fn&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;main&lt;/span&gt;() {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; data &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; get_data(); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// future not polled!
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;println!&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;{}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, data);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 2: Missing runtime
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;async&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;fn&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;do_work&lt;/span&gt;() { &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;println!&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;async work&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;); }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;fn&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;main&lt;/span&gt;() { do_work(); } &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// does nothing
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 3: Non-Send future
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;use&lt;/span&gt; std::rc::Rc;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;#[tokio::main]&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;async&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;fn&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;main&lt;/span&gt;() {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; data &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; Rc::new(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;42&lt;/span&gt;); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Rc is not Send
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; tokio::task::spawn(&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;async&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;move&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;println!&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;{}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, data);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }).&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;await&lt;/span&gt;.unwrap(); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// ERROR: future !Send
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 4: Blocking in async
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;#[tokio::main]&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;async&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;fn&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;main&lt;/span&gt;() {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; std::thread::sleep(std::time::Duration::from_secs(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;5&lt;/span&gt;)); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// blocks runtime
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="solutions"&gt;Solutions&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-always-await-futures"&gt;Fix 1: Always .await futures&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-rust" data-lang="rust"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;async&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;fn&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;get_data&lt;/span&gt;() -&amp;gt; String { &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;data&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;.to_string() }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;#[tokio::main]&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;async&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;fn&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;main&lt;/span&gt;() {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; data &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; get_data().&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;await&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;println!&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;{}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, data);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-use-a-runtime-for-async-code"&gt;Fix 2: Use a runtime for async code&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-rust" data-lang="rust"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;async&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;fn&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;do_work&lt;/span&gt;() -&amp;gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;i32&lt;/span&gt; { &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;42&lt;/span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;#[tokio::main]&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;async&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;fn&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;main&lt;/span&gt;() {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; result &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; do_work().&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;await&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;println!&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Result: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;{}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, result);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-use-arc-instead-of-rc-for-async-tasks"&gt;Fix 3: Use Arc instead of Rc for async tasks&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-rust" data-lang="rust"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;use&lt;/span&gt; std::sync::Arc;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;#[tokio::main]&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;async&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;fn&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;main&lt;/span&gt;() {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; data &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; Arc::new(&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;42&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; tokio::task::spawn(&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;async&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;move&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;println!&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;{}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, data);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }).&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;await&lt;/span&gt;.unwrap();
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-4-use-spawn_blocking-for-sync-operations"&gt;Fix 4: Use spawn_blocking for sync operations&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-rust" data-lang="rust"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;#[tokio::main]&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;async&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;fn&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;main&lt;/span&gt;() {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; data &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; tokio::task::spawn_blocking(&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;||&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; std::fs::read_to_string(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;file.txt&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;).unwrap()
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }).&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;await&lt;/span&gt;.unwrap();
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;println!&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Read &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;{}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt; bytes&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, data.len());
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-rust" data-lang="rust"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;async&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;fn&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;hello&lt;/span&gt;() { &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;println!&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Hello from async!&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;); }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;fn&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;main&lt;/span&gt;() {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; hello(); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Does nothing — future not polled
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;println!&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;This prints, but hello() doesn&amp;#39;t&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Output:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Rust Async/Await Error — Async Function Not Found</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/rust/async-await/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/rust/async-await/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="asyncawait-error--async-function-not-found"&gt;Async/Await Error — Async Function Not Found&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Errors related to async/await in Rust include messages like &amp;ldquo;async function not found&amp;rdquo;, &amp;ldquo;future is not Send&amp;rdquo;, or &amp;ldquo;missing async runtime&amp;rdquo;. These occur when async code is misused or when the async ecosystem is not properly configured.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Rust&amp;rsquo;s async/await is zero-cost and requires a runtime (like tokio) to execute. The compiler generates state machines for async functions, but doesn&amp;rsquo;t include a runtime. Common issues:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Rust Future Is Not Send / Not a Future — Async Error Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/rust/async-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/rust/async-error/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="future-is-not-send--not-a-future"&gt;Future Is Not Send / Not a Future&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The error &lt;code&gt;future is not Send&lt;/code&gt; or &lt;code&gt;the trait Send is not implemented&lt;/code&gt; occurs when you try to spawn an async task on a multithreaded runtime, but the future captures a type that is not &lt;code&gt;Send&lt;/code&gt;-safe. The error &lt;code&gt;not a future&lt;/code&gt; occurs when you use &lt;code&gt;.await&lt;/code&gt; on a value that does not implement the &lt;code&gt;Future&lt;/code&gt; trait.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tokio and other multithreaded async runtimes require futures to be &lt;code&gt;Send&lt;/code&gt; so they can be moved between threads. Types like &lt;code&gt;Rc&amp;lt;T&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;*const T&lt;/code&gt;, and raw pointers are not &lt;code&gt;Send&lt;/code&gt; because they are not safe to access from multiple threads. If a future captures any non-&lt;code&gt;Send&lt;/code&gt; type, it cannot be spawned on a multithreaded runtime.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Async error</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/dart/async-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/dart/async-error/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An async error occurs when an error is thrown during asynchronous execution (in async functions or Futures) and isn&amp;rsquo;t properly caught. These errors can be unhandled if not using try-catch with await.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Unhandled exceptions in async functions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Not awaiting Futures that may fail&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Missing error callbacks on Futures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Network or I/O errors in async operations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-dart" data-lang="dart"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// WRONG: Not handling async errors
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Future&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; fetchData() &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;async&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;var&lt;/span&gt; response &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;await&lt;/span&gt; http.&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;get&lt;/span&gt;(Uri.parse(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;https://api.example.com&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;));
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; response.body; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// may throw
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// CORRECT: Use try-catch
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Future&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; fetchData() &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;async&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;try&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;var&lt;/span&gt; response &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;await&lt;/span&gt; http.&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;get&lt;/span&gt;(Uri.parse(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;https://api.example.com&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;));
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; response.body;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; } &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;catch&lt;/span&gt; (e) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;Error: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;$&lt;/span&gt;e&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-dart" data-lang="dart"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// WRONG: Not awaiting or handling Future
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;void&lt;/span&gt; main() {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; fetchData(); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Future not awaited, errors lost
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// CORRECT: Await and handle
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Future&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;void&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; main() &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;async&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;try&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;var&lt;/span&gt; data &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;await&lt;/span&gt; fetchData();
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; print(data);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; } &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;catch&lt;/span&gt; (e) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; print(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;Error: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;$&lt;/span&gt;e&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-dart" data-lang="dart"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Example 1: Unhandled Future error
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Future&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; divide(&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; a, &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; b) &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;async&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (b &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;==&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;throw&lt;/span&gt; Exception(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;Division by zero&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; a &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;~/&lt;/span&gt; b;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Missing await and error handling
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Example 2: Network error
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Future&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;void&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; fetchData() &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;async&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;var&lt;/span&gt; response &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;await&lt;/span&gt; http.&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;get&lt;/span&gt;(Uri.parse(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;invalid-url&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;));
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// May throw SocketException
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Example 3: JSON parse error
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Future&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;Map&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; parseJson(&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;String&lt;/span&gt; text) &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;async&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; json.decode(text); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// May throw FormatException
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/dart/null-check-error"&gt;Null check operator used on null&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/dart/type-cast-error"&gt;type cast error&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>Node.js UnhandledPromiseRejectionWarning</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/javascript/node-unhandled-rejection/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/javascript/node-unhandled-rejection/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;UnhandledPromiseRejectionWarning&lt;/code&gt; occurs when a Promise is rejected but no &lt;code&gt;.catch()&lt;/code&gt; handler or &lt;code&gt;await&lt;/code&gt; in a &lt;code&gt;try/catch&lt;/code&gt; is attached. In Node.js 15+, unhandled rejections crash the process by default.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Common unhandled rejection messages include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;UnhandledPromiseRejectionWarning: Error: something failed&lt;/code&gt; — no catch handler&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;UnhandledPromiseRejectionWarning: [object Object]&lt;/code&gt; — rejected with an object&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;UnhandledPromiseRejectionWarning: TypeError: cannot read property of undefined&lt;/code&gt; — async function throws&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-javascript" data-lang="javascript"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 1: Missing .catch() on promise
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;fetch&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;https://api.example.com/data&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; .&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;then&lt;/span&gt;((&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;res&lt;/span&gt;) =&amp;gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;res&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;json&lt;/span&gt;())
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; .&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;then&lt;/span&gt;((&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;data&lt;/span&gt;) =&amp;gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;console&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;log&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;data&lt;/span&gt;));
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// No .catch() — network errors become unhandled rejections
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 2: Async function without try/catch
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;async&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;function&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;getUser&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;id&lt;/span&gt;) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;res&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;await&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;fetch&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;`/api/users/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;${&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;id&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;`&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;res&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;json&lt;/span&gt;(); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// throws if response is not JSON
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 3: Fire-and-forget async calls
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;async&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;function&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;saveData&lt;/span&gt;() { &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;/* ... */&lt;/span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;saveData&lt;/span&gt;(); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// return value (promise) is ignored
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 4: Event handler throwing in async context
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;process&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;on&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;unhandledRejection&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, () =&amp;gt; {}); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// does NOT prevent crash in Node 15+
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="solutions"&gt;Solutions&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-add-proper-error-handling"&gt;Fix 1: Add proper error handling&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-javascript" data-lang="javascript"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Use .catch() on promise chains
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;fetch&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;https://api.example.com/data&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; .&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;then&lt;/span&gt;((&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;res&lt;/span&gt;) =&amp;gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;res&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;json&lt;/span&gt;())
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; .&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;then&lt;/span&gt;((&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;data&lt;/span&gt;) =&amp;gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;console&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;log&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;data&lt;/span&gt;))
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; .&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;catch&lt;/span&gt;((&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;err&lt;/span&gt;) =&amp;gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;console&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;error&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Fetch failed:&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;err&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;message&lt;/span&gt;));
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Use try/catch with async/await
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;async&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;function&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;fetchData&lt;/span&gt;() {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;try&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;res&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;await&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;fetch&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;https://api.example.com/data&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;await&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;res&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;json&lt;/span&gt;();
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; } &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;catch&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;err&lt;/span&gt;) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;console&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;error&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Fetch failed:&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;err&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;message&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-global-unhandled-rejection-handler"&gt;Fix 2: Global unhandled rejection handler&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-javascript" data-lang="javascript"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;process&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;on&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;unhandledRejection&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, (&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;reason&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;promise&lt;/span&gt;) =&amp;gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;console&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;error&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Unhandled Rejection at:&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;promise&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;reason:&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;reason&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Log to error reporting service
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Sentry.captureException(reason);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;});
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Note: This does NOT prevent the process from exiting in Node 15+
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Fix the actual unhandled rejection instead
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-ensure-all-async-calls-are-awaited"&gt;Fix 3: Ensure all async calls are awaited&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-javascript" data-lang="javascript"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Bad: fire-and-forget
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;async&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;function&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;processRequest&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;req&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;res&lt;/span&gt;) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;await&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;saveToDatabase&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;req&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;body&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;saveAuditLog&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;req&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;body&lt;/span&gt;); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// not awaited — unhandled rejection possible
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;res&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;send&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;ok&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Good: await or catch all async operations
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;async&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;function&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;processRequest&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;req&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;res&lt;/span&gt;) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;await&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;saveToDatabase&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;req&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;body&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;await&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;saveAuditLog&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;req&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;body&lt;/span&gt;); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// or: saveAuditLog(req.body).catch(console.error)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;res&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;send&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;ok&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-javascript" data-lang="javascript"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Unhandled rejection: promise returned but never handled
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;async&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;function&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;riskyOperation&lt;/span&gt;() {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;throw&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; Error(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Database connection failed&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Bad — return value is ignored
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;riskyOperation&lt;/span&gt;();
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Good — handled with try/catch
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;try&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;await&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;riskyOperation&lt;/span&gt;();
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;} &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;catch&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;err&lt;/span&gt;) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;console&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;error&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Operation failed:&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;err&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;message&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/javascript/uncaught-promise/"&gt;Uncaught Exception&lt;/a&gt; — synchronous uncaught exception.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/javascript/err_stream_destroyed/"&gt;ERR_STREAM_DESTROYED&lt;/a&gt; — stream destroyed before operation completes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/javascript/internalerror/"&gt;InternalError&lt;/a&gt; — internal Node.js error.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>